    "overview_title": "No Substitute for Hard Work",
    "overview_subtitle": "Evaluating Algebraic Expressions",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students transfer their understanding of numeric expressions to algebraic expressions. They learn to distinguish between linear and nonlinear expressions, combine like terms with rational coefficients, and substitute values to verify equivalency. Students then apply these skills to write algebraic expressions representing problem situations and use substitution to find solutions."
  },
